  "read": [
    "The two graders are DIFFERENTLY WRONG, which is the property #1005 asks for - an instrument needs independence, not superiority. Gemma caught two real, reachable, untested defects in shipped 30B-authored battery code that our 14B scored clean; the 14B caught a correctness defect in the synthetic module that Gemma scored clean.",
    "The 14B's apparent 0/9 non-determinism in arm A is overwhelmingly an artefact of the UNCONSTRAINED probe path. On the production grammar-constrained path it is 8/9 verdict-stable over 3 runs/cell. Any claim that the production juror is unstable must be made against arm C, not arm A.",
    "Because arm A's 14B verdicts were unstable, the 13/36 field disagreement count is an UPPER BOUND that mixes real cross-model difference with 14B run-to-run noise. It is not a rate."
  ],
  "not_measured": [
    "Gemma on the grammar-constrained path (arm C ran the 14B only) - so the cross-model comparison is unconstrained-vs-unconstrained, and a constrained head-to-head is unmeasured",
    "N>1 subject counts per defect class - 3 subjects is a FAILURE SHAPE, not a rate; nothing here supports a percentage claim about either grader",
    "speculative decoding (production runs the 14B with a pruned 0.6B draft; both arms ran without it)",
    "the full green_quality jury path (3 jurors + per-field majority + abstain) - this measures single-juror emissions, not the tallied verdict production actually uses",
    "any answer_quality golden-set re-scoring, so the same-family INFLATION estimate #1005 wants is still unmeasured",
    "Gemma co-residency with the 14B (sequential loads only)",
    "sustained thermals, power, multi-seed variance beyond the runs stated"
